OL,7,F"There is a long history of children
OL,8,Ffeeling sick at the camp over many
OL,9,Fyears."
OL,11,FThe rented premises, Stathern Lodge,
OL,12,Fwere not connected to the camp itself,
OL,13,Fthe court heard, and Ruben was in
OL,14,Fcharge of youngsters there, Ms Prior
OL,15,Fsaid.
OL,17,F"He made the rules," she added. "For
OL,18,Fmany years he has played what he calls
OL,19,Fa sweet game with the children in
OL,20,Fwhich he goes into the bedrooms.
